xwikidoc.title: PhenoTips: phenotyping made easy
xwikidoc.content:
(% class="link-box" %)((( (% class="link demo" %)[[Demo>>data.WebHome]]
(% class="link source-code" %)[[Code>>https://github.com/phenotips/phenotips/]] ([[LGPL 2.1>>Community.License]])
(% class="link download" %)[[Download>>PhenoTips.Download||title="Download PhenoTips for MacOS, Linux and Windows"]]
(% class="link team" %)[[Team: Compbio UofT>>http://www.cs.toronto.edu/~~brudno/group.html]] ))) //PhenoTips// is an open source software tool for collecting and analyzing phenotypic information for patients with genetic disorders. Our software combines an easy-to-use interface, compatible with any device that runs a Web browser, with a standardized database back-end. The PhenoTips’ user interface closely mirrors clinician workflows so as to facilitate the recording of observations made during the patient encounter. By collecting, classifying and analyzing phenotypic information during the patient encounter, PhenoTips allows for streamlining of clinic workflow, efficient data entry, improved diagnosis, standardization of collected patient phenotypes, and sharing of anonymized patient phenotype data for the study of rare disorders.
(% class="clearfloats" %)((()))
(% style="width: 49%; float: left" %)((( == Features ==
Collected data include * demographics * medical history * family history * physical and laboratory measurements * physical findings * additional notes
Phenotypic information is represented using the [[Human Phenotype Ontology (HPO)>>http://human-phenotype-ontology.org/]]; however the complexity of the ontology is hidden behind a user interface which combines //simple selection of common phenotypes// with //error-tolerant, predictive search of the entire ontology//.
//PhenoTips// automatically analyzes a wide range of measurements and plots live the corresponding growth curves. Additionally, it supports accurate diagnosis by analyzing the entered data, then suggesting additional clinical investigations and providing OMIM links to likely disorders.
== Contact == Ask for support: [[##support@phenotips.org##>>mailto:support@phenotips.org]] Get the latest news: [[##announcements@phenotips.org##>>http://mail.phenotips.org/mailman/listinfo/announcements]] Follow us on twitter: [[@phenotips>>https://twitter.com/phenotips]] )))

== Citing PhenoTips == If you wish to mention PhenoTips in a scientific article, please refer to our [[paper published in May 2013 in //Human Mutation//>>http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/humu.22347/abstract]]:
> Girdea, M., Dumitriu, S., Fiume, M., Bowdin, S., Boycott, K. M., Chénier, S., Chitayat, D., Faghfoury, H., Meyn, M. S., Ray, P. N., So, J., Stavropoulos, D. J. and Brudno, M. (2013), PhenoTips: Patient Phenotyping Software for Clinical and Research Use. Hum. Mutat., 34: 1057–1065. doi: 10.1002/humu.22347
